      • PROPERTY_CHANGE_SNAPSHOT_OWNER

        static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_CHANGE_SNAPSHOT_OWNER
        Build property identifying whether or not to make the deliver target the owner of the delivered snapshot. This will only be done if 'ALL' components have been delivered to the deliver target.
        Since:
        0.9.0 (RTC 4.0)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PROPERTY_FORCE_REPLACE

        static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_FORCE_REPLACE
        Build property identifying whether or not to force a component replace even if the deliver target is already at the specific baseline. It is recommended not to do this as duplicate baseline entries will appear in history. I.e builds can be triggered if changes are introduced into ComponentA however ComponentB which did not change would end up having the same baseline replaced in the deliver target unnecessarily. Note: Prior to RTC 6.0.2, it would always perform the replace.
        Since:
        0.11.0.2 (RTC 6.0.2)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PROPERTY_HOURS_TO_GO_BACK

        static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_HOURS_TO_GO_BACK
        Build property identifying the number of hours to go back when querying for build results. Example: "Search through all build results from the last 24 hours".
        The default value will be 24 hours, however as a rough rule of thumb, set this value to 5 times the average build length. The returned build results are used to determine if we should abort the auto deliver or not. For example, if another build with a more recent 'accept' snapshot finished before this one has finished, we would want to abort the auto deliver as we would be delivering an older snapshot.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PROPERTY_RETRY_ATTEMPTS

        static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_RETRY_ATTEMPTS
        Build property identifying the maximum number of times to attempt the auto deliver if a StaleDataException is thrown. The exception could be a result of an older build finishing around the time the current build's auto deliver took place. This should not prevent the current build from performing the auto deliver and so we will retry to see if we should deliver or not. The default value will be 3, however if a continuous auto deliver build is set up such that it occurs frequently and has a short build time, perhaps raising this value will help.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
